A bandh was observed in Andhra University on Friday in protest against the recent suicide of a Dalit research scholar of University of Hyderabad Rohith and seeking action against UoH Vice-Chancellor and resignations of Union Ministers Smriti Irani and Bandaru Dattatreya.The bandh call, given by students and research scholars, SC, ST and BC Employees and students associations, all students unions received total response.The students, teachers and employees gathered in front of Dr. Ambedkarâ€™s statue on the campus and after garlanding a photo of Rohith went in a rally to the Collectorate. A memorandum was submitted to the Collector.Protests were held at different places in the city and district, including Agency area against the death of Rohith.